## Semantic Color Tokens (USE THESE IN PLUGINS)

### Action
- `--color-action-complementary`: --color-pepper-80 /* Used for complementary primary button backgrounds. Must be used with complementary backgrounds. */
- `--color-action-complementary-active`: --color-pepper-100 /* Used for complementary primary button backgrounds in the active state. Must be used with complementary backgrounds. */
- `--color-action-complementary-border`: --color-white /* Used for the border of secondary buttons on dark backgrounds with a complementary container background. */
- `--color-action-complementary-focus`: --color-pepper-80 /* Used for complementary primary button backgrounds in the focus state. Must be used with complementary backgrounds. */
- `--color-action-complementary-hover`: --color-pepper-90 /* Used for complementary primary button backgrounds in the hover state. Must be used with complementary backgrounds. */
- `--color-action-complementary-subtle`: --color-white /* Background color intended to be very light or invisible on complementary/dark backgrounds in the default state. Use for complementary secondary and tertiary button backgrounds, as well as icon control fill colors on complementary/dark backgrounds. */
- `--color-action-complementary-subtle-active`: --color-white /* Complementary passive secondary/tertiary button background color in an active state; to be used with complementary backgrounds */
- `--color-action-complementary-subtle-focus`: --color-white /* Complementary passive secondary/tertiary button background color in a focus state; to be used with complementary backgrounds */
- `--color-action-complementary-subtle-hover`: --color-white /* Used to render secondary buttons, tertiary buttons, and icon control fill colors on dark backgrounds with a complementary container background. Applied in the hover state. */
- `--color-action-negative`: --color-ui-negative /* Used for destructive primary button backgrounds, destructive secondary/tertiary button text, and destructive secondary border colors. */
- `--color-action-negative-active`: --color-ui-negative-active /* Used for destructive primary button backgrounds in the active state. */
- `--color-action-negative-focus`: --color-ui-negative /* Used for destructive primary button backgrounds in the focus state. */
- `--color-action-negative-hover`: --color-ui-negative-hover /* Used for destructive primary button backgrounds in the hover state. */
- `--color-action-negative-subtle`: --color-watermelon-70 /* Used for destructive secondary/tertiary button backgrounds. Subtle tokens are for backgrounds that are not visible or very light. */
- `--color-action-negative-subtle-active`: --color-watermelon-70 /* Used for destructive secondary/tertiary button backgrounds in the active state. Subtle tokens are for backgrounds that are not visible or very light. */
- `--color-action-negative-subtle-focus`: --color-watermelon-70 /* Used for destructive secondary/tertiary button backgrounds in the focus state. Subtle tokens are for backgrounds that are not visible or very light. */
- `--color-action-negative-subtle-hover`: --color-watermelon-70 /* Used for destructive secondary/tertiary button backgrounds in the hover state. Subtle tokens are for backgrounds that are not visible or very light. */
- `--color-action-passive`: --color-pepper-10 /* Used for passive button backgrounds. Passive buttons are for actions unrelated to the primary action—optional or less important than the primary action. */
- `--color-action-passive-active`: --color-pepper-30 /* Used for passive button backgrounds in the active state. Passive buttons are for actions unrelated to the primary action—optional or less important than the primary action. */
- `--color-action-passive-border`: --color-pepper-20 /* Passive button border color */
- `--color-action-passive-focus`: --color-pepper-10 /* Used for passive button backgrounds in the focus state. Passive buttons are for actions unrelated to the primary action—optional or less important than the primary action. */
- `--color-action-passive-hover`: --color-pepper-20 /* Used for passive button backgrounds in the hover state. Passive buttons are for actions unrelated to the primary action—optional or less important than the primary action. */
- `--color-action-passive-subtle`: --color-pepper-60 /* Used for passive buttons that require a background color that is not visible or very light in the default state. Commonly used on passive secondary and tertiary buttons. */
- `--color-action-passive-subtle-active`: --color-pepper-60 /* Used for passive buttons that require a background color that is not visible or very light in the active state. Commonly used on passive secondary and tertiary buttons. */
- `--color-action-passive-subtle-focus`: --color-pepper-60 /* Used for passive buttons that require a background color that is not visible or very light in the focus state. Commonly used on passive secondary and tertiary buttons. */
- `--color-action-passive-subtle-hover`: --color-pepper-60 /* Used for passive buttons that require a background color that is not visible or very light in the hover state. Commonly used on passive secondary and tertiary buttons. */
- `--color-action-special-use`: --color-blueberry-70 /* Special use should only be used in race occurrences for marketing upsells to have a customer purchase or upgrade their product or service. Used for special use primary button backgrounds, special use secondary/tertiary button text, and special use secondary button border colors. */
- `--color-action-special-use-active`: --color-blueberry-90 /* Used for special use primary button backgrounds in the active state. Special use should only be used in race occurrences for marketing upsells to have a customer purchase or upgrade their product or service. */
- `--color-action-special-use-focus`: --color-blueberry-70 /* Used for special use primary button backgrounds in the focus state. Special use should only be used in race occurrences for marketing upsells to have a customer purchase or upgrade their product or service. */
- `--color-action-special-use-hover`: --color-blueberry-80 /* Used for special use primary button backgrounds in the hover state. Special use should only be used in race occurrences for marketing upsells to have a customer purchase or upgrade their product or service. */
- `--color-action-special-use-subtle`: --color-blueberry-70 /* Used for special use secondary/tertiary button backgrounds. Subtle tokens are for backgrounds that are not visible or very light. Special use should only be used in race occurrences for marketing upsells to have a customer purchase or upgrade their product or service. */
- `--color-action-special-use-subtle-active`: --color-blueberry-70 /* Used for special use secondary/tertiary button backgrounds in the active state. Subtle tokens are for backgrounds that are not visible or very light. Special use should only be used in race occurrences for marketing upsells to have a customer purchase or upgrade their product or service. */
- `--color-action-special-use-subtle-focus`: --color-blueberry-70 /* Used for special use secondary/tertiary button backgrounds in the focus state. Subtle tokens are for backgrounds that are not visible or very light. Special use should only be used in race occurrences for marketing upsells to have a customer purchase or upgrade their product or service. */
- `--color-action-special-use-subtle-hover`: --color-blueberry-70 /* Used for special use secondary/tertiary button backgrounds in the hover state. Subtle tokens are for backgrounds that are not visible or very light. Special use should only be used in race occurrences for marketing upsells to have a customer purchase or upgrade their product or service. */
- `--color-action-standard`: --color-ui-primary /* Used for primary button backgrounds, secondary/tertiary button text, and secondary border colors. */
- `--color-action-standard-active`: --color-ui-primary-active /* Used for primary button backgrounds in the active state. */
- `--color-action-standard-focus`: --color-ui-primary-focus /* Used for primary button backgrounds in the focus state. */
- `--color-action-standard-hover`: --color-ui-primary-hover /* Used for primary button backgrounds in the hover state. */
- `--color-action-standard-subtle`: --color-spearmint-80 /* Used for secondary and tertiary button backgrounds. */
- `--color-action-standard-subtle-active`: --color-spearmint-80 /* Used for secondary and tertiary button backgrounds in the active state. */
- `--color-action-standard-subtle-focus`: --color-spearmint-80 /* Used for secondary and tertiary button backgrounds in the focus state. */
- `--color-action-standard-subtle-hover`: --color-spearmint-80 /* Used for secondary and tertiary button backgrounds in the hover state. */

### Code
- `--color-code-attribute`: --color-kiwi-80 /* Used for attribute text when writing code. */
- `--color-code-boolean`: --color-eggplant-90 /* Used for boolean text when writing code. */
- `--color-code-comment`: --color-text-quaternary /* Used for comment text when writing code. */
- `--color-code-keyword`: --color-dragonfruit-70 /* Used for writing text code and differentiating the keyword text. */
- `--color-code-line-highlight`: --color-pepper-0 /* Used for highlighting text code. */
- `--color-code-line-number`: --color-pepper-60 /* Used for writing text code and differentiating the line number text. */
- `--color-code-number`: --color-persimmon-70 /* Used for number text when writing code. */
- `--color-code-operator`: --color-pepper-60 /* Used for writing text code and differentiating the operator text. */
- `--color-code-qualifier`: --color-kiwi-50 /* Used for writing text code and differentiating the qualifier text. */
- `--color-code-string`: --color-agave-80 /* Used for string text when writing code. */
- `--color-code-text`: --color-pepper-120 /* Used for writing text code and differentiating the code text. */
- `--color-code-type`: --color-persimmon-40 /* Used for writing text code and differentiating the type text. */
- `--color-code-variable-1`: --color-pepper-120 /* Used for writing text code and differentiating the primary variable text. */
- `--color-code-variable-2`: --color-pepper-120 /* Used for writing text code and differentiating the secondary variable text. */
- `--color-code-variable-3`: --color-persimmon-40 /* Used for writing text code and differentiating the tertiary variable text. */

### Container
- `--color-container-background-accent`: --color-blueberry-10 /* Optional background for brand expression to accent and differentiate content and layout. Either low-contrast or a subtle color value. */
- `--color-container-background-accent-active`: --color-blueberry-30 /* Optional, brand expression, container background to accent and differentiate content and layout in the active state. It is either low-contrast or subtle color value. */
- `--color-container-background-accent-focus`: --color-blueberry-10 /* Optional, brand expression, container background to accent and differentiate content and layout in the focus state. It is either low-contrast or subtle color value. */
- `--color-container-background-accent-hover`: --color-blueberry-20 /* Optional, brand expression, container background to accent and differentiate content and layout in the hover state. It is either low-contrast or subtle color value. */
- `--color-container-background-accent-selected`: --color-blueberry-30 /* Optional, brand expression, container background to accent and differentiate content and layout in the selected state. It is either low-contrast or subtle color value. */
- `--color-container-background-attention`: --color-persimmon-10 /* Background color for containers with 'soft negative' sentiment content. For example, used on search highlights to bring attention to relevant/matching areas. */
- `--color-container-background-attention-secondary`: --color-persimmon-20 /* Secondary background color for containers with "soft negative" sentiment content. Use when more visual prominence is needed than the primary attention background. This token needs to have higher contrast visibility and must be darker than —color-container-background-attention. When using text it must be paired with —color-text-primary. For example Secondary Text Badge. */
- `--color-container-background-attention-tertiary`: --color-page-background-primary /* Tertiary background color for containers with "soft negative" sentiment content. Lightest variation for subtle emphasis. Commonly used in page messages when minimal visual prominence is needed. */
- `--color-container-background-beta`: --color-agave-10 /* Used as background color for containers with beta content. */
- `--color-container-background-beta-secondary`: --color-page-background-primary /* Secondary background color for containers with "beta" content. Use when more visual prominence is needed than the primary beta background. This token needs to have higher contrast visibility and must be darker than —color-container-background-beta. When using text it must be paired with —color-text-primary. For example Secondary Text Badge. */
- `--color-container-background-beta-tertiary`: --color-page-background-primary /* Tertiary background color for containers with "beta" content. Lightest variation for subtle emphasis. Commonly used in page messages when minimal visual prominence is needed. */
- `--color-container-background-complementary`: --color-pepper-120 /* Used for containers that are dark in both light and dark modes. Common in tooltips and similar components. To ensure dark mode stays dark, follow these contrast ratios: light mode 11:1, dark mode 1.3:1. */
- `--color-container-background-info`: --color-blueberry-10 /* Background color for containers with informative content. */
- `--color-container-background-info-secondary`: --color-blueberry-20 /* Secondary background color for small components and containers with informative content. Use when more visual prominence is needed than the primary info background. This token needs to have higher contrast visibility and must be darker than —color-container-background-info. When using text it must be paired with —color-text-primary. For example Secondary Text Badge. */
- `--color-container-background-info-tertiary`: --color-page-background-primary /* Tertiary background color for containers with informative content. Lightest variation for subtle emphasis. Commonly used in page messages when minimal visual prominence is needed. */
- `--color-container-background-inverse`: --color-pepper-120 /* Dark background color for containers in light mode not to be confused with complementary tokens. This color is always an inverse of color-page-background-primary. Use sparingly because of the brightness in dark mode and preferably use complementary tokens which have a much larger set that work together and do not have such a bright level in dark mode. */
- `--color-container-background-negative`: --color-watermelon-10 /* Background color for containers with negative content. */
- `--color-container-background-negative-secondary`: --color-watermelon-20 /* Secondary background color for small components and containers with negative content. Use when more visual prominence is needed than the primary negative background. This token needs to have higher contrast visibility and must be darker than —color-container-background-negative. When using text it must be paired with —color-text-primary. For example Secondary Text Badge. */
- `--color-container-background-negative-tertiary`: --color-page-background-primary /* Tertiary background color for containers with negative content. Lightest variation for subtle emphasis. Commonly used in page messages when minimal visual prominence is needed. */
- `--color-container-background-neutral`: --color-pepper-10 /* Used as background color for containers with neutral content, undefined content, or placeholders. */
- `--color-container-background-neutral-secondary`: --color-page-background-primary /* Secondary background color for containers with "neutral" sentiment content. Use when more visual prominence is needed than the primary neutral background. This token needs to have higher contrast visibility and must be darker than —color-container-background-neutral. When using text it must be paired with —color-text-primary. For example Secondary Text Badge. */
